<subSubSection id="08B65368E8B492D0D28B0B5E71E2C14F" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="description">
<paragraph id="2F3DD582CE9D639EBC125ACD1954D461" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Systematic position and characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="96482CD176A6599CB37AAEC219FBA6B7" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName id="B5129F839F67DEEE0F236A583C65272E" authority="Braasch &amp; Soldan, 1980" authorityName="Braasch &amp; Soldan" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Centroptella" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5CA52F1C943E6E022BD99550D1322CEB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Centroptella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by an unusual combination of characters: on one hand, it undoubtedly belongs to the holophyletic taxon Baetovectata Kluge &amp; Novikova, 2011, based on (1) presence of two marginal intercalaries in each space of wing (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="16F30B0493EE9D699EB29CA34E10FA48" captionStart="Figures 149–152" captionStartId="F20" captionText="Figures 149 - 152. Centroptella of group inzingae - ingridae. Centroptella ingridae sp. nov. (holotype), fore wing 150 Centroptella inzingae (lectotype), genitalia (gv gonovectis us proximal margin of unistyliger) 151 - 152 Centroptella saxophila, gonovectes (specimens reared from larvae by N. Kluge in the Western Cape Province of South Africa)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.914.46652.figures149-152" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/382015" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">149</figureCitation>
), (2) narrow and arched gonovectes of the penis (Figs 
<figureCitation id="C3640CD32EDB9AFB7F1C3F975BBDB8B7" captionStart="Figures 77–80" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figures 77 - 80. Male genitalia of Centroptella longisetosa. 77 - 79 specimens from India: (77) genitalia of imago (78) subimaginal exuviae (79) subimaginal gonostyli crumpled under larval cuticle (80) paratype of C. liebenauae (possibly reared from neotype): genitalia of imago." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.914.46652.figures77-80" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/382003" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">77-80</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="72ED9CB789897FB19469BF9C372F83F3" captionStart="Figures 138–143" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figures 138 - 143. Centroptella ingridae sp. nov. (specimens from Thailand). 138 abdominal sterna and terga of female imago 139 the same, male imago 140 - 143 genitalia of male imago (139 - 141 holotype)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.914.46652.figures138-143" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/382013" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">141-143</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BCB3E26DD00D80D40BDCAFDF43F252E2" captionStart="Figures 144–148" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figures 144 - 148. Centroptella ingridae sp. nov. (specimens from Thailand). 144 - 145 left and right mandibles 146 genitalia of male imago 147 their subimaginal exuviae 148 subimaginal gonostyli crumpled under larval cuticle (146 - 147 holotype)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.914.46652.figures144-148" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/382014" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">146</figureCitation>
, 150152) and (3) medially inclined subimaginal gonostyli when they are developing under the larval cuticle (Figs 
<figureCitation id="73F5AC8E65C4F6B2B6B769DA564E4401" captionStart="Figures 77–80" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figures 77 - 80. Male genitalia of Centroptella longisetosa. 77 - 79 specimens from India: (77) genitalia of imago (78) subimaginal exuviae (79) subimaginal gonostyli crumpled under larval cuticle (80) paratype of C. liebenauae (possibly reared from neotype): genitalia of imago." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.914.46652.figures77-80" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/382003" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">79</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F5139A75B661C6750B50A97167599BB9" captionStart="Figures 144–148" captionStartId="F19" captionText="Figures 144 - 148. Centroptella ingridae sp. nov. (specimens from Thailand). 144 - 145 left and right mandibles 146 genitalia of male imago 147 their subimaginal exuviae 148 subimaginal gonostyli crumpled under larval cuticle (146 - 147 holotype)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.914.46652.figures144-148" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/382014" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">148</figureCitation>
). The taxon Baetovectata belongs to the holophyletic taxon Anteropatellata Kluge, 1997, which is characterized by the presence of a patella-tibial suture on the forelegs of the larva and female imago and subimago. On the other hand, the leg structure of 
<taxonomicName id="5C8D4F26339D4E32EF8278D4156223C3" authority="Braasch &amp; Soldan, 1980" authorityName="Braasch &amp; Soldan" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Centroptella" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2556F0945A8274DBAF393FE1B3EA85EF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Centroptella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not conform with the characteristics of Anteropatellata. The larva of 
<taxonomicName id="69FC00CE15686621C6342717AF7C7F9F" authority="Braasch &amp; Soldan, 1980" authorityName="Braasch &amp; Soldan" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Centroptella" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AA64FBDCF2C2267B191DC67682FC32A4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Centroptella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the structure of the tibia modified and different on each pair of legs, so that the patella-tibial suture is absent on forelegs and greatly shifted distally on the middle and hind legs; a row of long setae, which in some other taxa forms a transverse arc, in 
<taxonomicName id="D0D461ACB5A7BE638E2C4D594DB171AA" authority="Braasch &amp; Soldan, 1980" authorityName="Braasch &amp; Soldan" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Centroptella" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3843A2F611F2443B1902A7681BC45D54" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Centroptella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is greatly stretched along the tibia, being different on the fore, middle and hind legs (Figs 
<figureCitation id="92CF3524D4D9F62583BE08F79F9D5F78" captionStart="Figures 16–18" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 16 - 18. Centroptella illiesi, tibiae of fore, middle and hind legs, view from anterior side (bases of long setae shown both on anterior and posterior sides)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.914.46652.figures16-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/381997" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">16-18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="AB74AAA7ADF4D144DF1A3D611E66AC1B" captionStart="Figures 49–52" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 49 - 52. Centroptella longisetosa. 49 - 51 paratype of C. longisetosa: tibiae of fore, middle and hind legs, view from anterior side (bases of long setae shown both on anterior and posterior sides) 52 neotype of C. liebenauae (actually C. longisetosa): tenth abdominal segment without caudalii, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.914.46652.figures49-52" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/382000" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">49-51</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C9690DF42C0245FD160F2C220F55D441" captionStart="Figures 90–93" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figures 90 - 93. Centroptella ingridae sp. nov. (holotype). 90 - 92 tibia of fore, middle and hind leg, view from anterior side (bases of long setae shown both on anterior and posterior sides) 93 tenth abdominal segment without caudalii, ventral view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.914.46652.figures90-93" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/382006" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">90-92</figureCitation>
); the female imago and subimago of 
<taxonomicName id="BB36CEEA1B0D676499EE18838C8A3E71" authority="Braasch &amp; Soldan, 1980" authorityName="Braasch &amp; Soldan" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Centroptella" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="76F3D7E8F9C6812C39C56E0477A31237" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Centroptella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the usual leg structure, with the patella-tibial suture not shifted distally, but without patella-tibial suture on forelegs. This leg structure is characteristic of the plesiomorphon Protopatellata Kluge &amp; Novikova, 2011 and has striking similarity with the Afrotropical taxon 
<taxonomicName id="38D70385B446C3EA3C9BE2FBB6BB285A" authority="Gillies, 1990" authorityName="Gillies" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Potamocloeon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Potamocloeon" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="307AADC2609FEDBA641EA1689240F9F5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Potamocloeon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gillies, 1990 (= 
<taxonomicName id="AE6C87C46FB67FD80E5D7A8EBDFE7029" authority="Lugo-Ortiz &amp; McCafferty, 1997" authorityName="Lugo-Ortiz &amp; McCafferty" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Maliqua" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maliqua" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C1CE5ADD0BA47487890D7F30EE2A98EE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Maliqua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lugo-Ortiz &amp; McCafferty, 1997), which undoubtedly belongs to Protopatellata and has no features of Baetovectata (
<bibRefCitation id="D95DA5C387B5D801DB9A5DC63FEE660D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4648.2.6" author="Kluge, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="299 - 317" refId="B15" refString="Kluge, NJ, 2019. Potamocloeon edentatum sp. nov. from Usambara Mountains in Tanzania (Ephemeroptera, Baetidae). Zootaxa 4648 (2): 299 - 317, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4648.2.6" title="Potamocloeon edentatum sp. nov. from Usambara Mountains in Tanzania (Ephemeroptera, Baetidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4648.2.6" volume="4648" year="2019">Kluge 2019</bibRefCitation>
). The Neotropical genus 
<taxonomicName id="5177FFDBEB805E8C8159F6F672FB28E9" authorityName="Traver" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Cloeodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cloeodes" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7B84D21B6CA77686786E344AF7E971B0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Cloeodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Traver, 1938, which some authors have confused with 
<taxonomicName id="6B0309810B6B5F0736C72DE8D134A33C" authority="Braasch &amp; Soldan, 1980" authorityName="Braasch &amp; Soldan" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Centroptella" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E23D46C1E5FB2892C16EBA535C6C11B9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Centroptella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above), has none of these features, and its larval and imaginal leg structure is typical for Anteropatellata (
<bibRefCitation id="527456614EA575DD5BEFCFF5AB94718C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4319.1.5" author="Kluge, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" pagination="91 - 127" refId="B14" refString="Kluge, NJ, 2017. Contribution to the knowledge of Cloeodes Traver 1938 (Ephemeroptera, Baetidae). Zootaxa 4319: 91 - 127, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4319.1.5" title="Contribution to the knowledge of Cloeodes Traver 1938 (Ephemeroptera, Baetidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4319.1.5" volume="4319" year="2017">Kluge 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="2EF09AD48FB6AA6C3B57537032DA4ADE" doi="10.3897/zookeys.914.46652.figures16-18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/381997" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" start="Figures 16–18" startId="F2">
<paragraph id="E27081FB6699AC4FA8A29C9D02813DCE" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<emphasis id="16595479726D824F0AD2E78DC401A52E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Figures 16-18.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="F57B78ECD751429A983034FD578D0DF9" authority="Braasch &amp; Soldán, 1980" authorityName="Braasch &amp; Soldán" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Centroptella illiesi" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="illiesi">
<emphasis id="085AA6D5141FFDCF315FFC4AE0F6AE36" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Centroptella illiesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, tibiae of fore, middle and hind legs, view from anterior side (bases of long setae shown both on anterior and posterior sides).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="BF7F0646E5A171F4594B66123C792BA9" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
Besides this paradoxical combination of baetovectatan and protopatellatan characters, 
<taxonomicName id="327030AF8D63878E715FB32F3BF1DEDF" authority="Braasch &amp; Soldan, 1980" authorityName="Braasch &amp; Soldan" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Centroptella" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A5BE8C4075C320C0A0158C7ED29FD4AD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Centroptella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an evident autapomorphy: secondary swimming setae on the outer sides of the larval cerci in the distal part of the cercus have oval transverse bases and form a regular row (Figs 
<figureCitation id="D98FC1F190684D52022583A461B4C5C2" captionStart="Figures 53–59" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figures 53 - 59. Larval exuviae of Centroptella longisetosa (neotype of C. liebenauae). 53 - 57 at the same magnification: (53) left half of pro- and mesonotum (54) thoracic pleura, left half of metanotum, fore- and hind legs (55) frons, antenna and labrum (56) tenth uromere and caudalii; (57) abdominal sterna and terga I-IX 58 margins of abdominal sterna IV-VII 59 cercus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.914.46652.figures53-59" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/382001" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">59</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="5EAF4DEE607E22A1EDB53E8E6CAD8473" captionStart="Figures 129–132" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figures 129 - 132. Centroptella ingridae sp. nov. (specimen from Thailand), exuviae of larval cercus (lateral view). 129 - 131 focus on lateral side to show bases of secondary swimming setae; 132 focus on median side to show bases of primary swimming setae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.914.46652.figures129-132" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/382011" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">129-131</figureCitation>
); in this respect, they resemble the primary swimming setae on the inner side of the cercus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8A9F0F231DB1B7F098840A74A9D10ABA" captionStart="Figures 129–132" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figures 129 - 132. Centroptella ingridae sp. nov. (specimen from Thailand), exuviae of larval cercus (lateral view). 129 - 131 focus on lateral side to show bases of secondary swimming setae; 132 focus on median side to show bases of primary swimming setae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.914.46652.figures129-132" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/382011" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">132</figureCitation>
), but they are smaller and less densely arranged.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0592C000A7E791EE908AFE163728A8F3" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
Another peculiar character of 
<taxonomicName id="28258853F914B85AB93897C3D1C08E2D" authority="Braasch &amp; Soldan, 1980" authorityName="Braasch &amp; Soldan" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Centroptella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Centroptella" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DFEE50B8B69422081E75D054C3F1B9F0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Centroptella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the presence of a pair of spaced transverse rows of long bifurcate setae on certain abdominal sterna of the larva (Figs 
<figureCitation id="0123F3BE39F02CF0339DB4911BCB9374" captionStart="Figures 53–59" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figures 53 - 59. Larval exuviae of Centroptella longisetosa (neotype of C. liebenauae). 53 - 57 at the same magnification: (53) left half of pro- and mesonotum (54) thoracic pleura, left half of metanotum, fore- and hind legs (55) frons, antenna and labrum (56) tenth uromere and caudalii; (57) abdominal sterna and terga I-IX 58 margins of abdominal sterna IV-VII 59 cercus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.914.46652.figures53-59" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/382001" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">58</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="09B42DFFD9FDE0BB08FE3AEA4C1EBB3F" captionStart="Figures 116–122" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figures 116 - 122. Centroptella ingridae sp. nov. (paratype of C. liebenauae), SEM photos of larva. 116 labrum 117 bifurcate setae on abdominal sternum IV 118 - 119 abdominal sterna IV-VI 120 - 121 paraprocts 122 flagellum of antenna." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.914.46652.figures116-122" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/382009" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">117-119</figureCitation>
); in different species these setal rows are present on sterna II-VI or on part of them, at least on sterna IV-V. Identical setal rows are found in a few other, non-related taxa (e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="E1FFBBCC5D685875BF83D26ECE2B784D" authority="Gillies, 1990" authorityName="Gillies" authorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Potamocloeon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Potamocloeon" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2A94DA48B728F0EE8BF1998B1329AC64" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Potamocloeon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gillies, 1990 and 
<taxonomicName id="7C526844EC8421F45FBE62ED5AB61B94" authorityName="Traver" authorityYear="1938" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Cloeodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cloeodes" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EAB1298238041CFEE1D95920DFBCD360" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Cloeodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Traver, 1938).
</paragraph>
